description: Good old ketchup, tastes great on hot dogs. This is a commercial version specifically engineered for long shelf life, so it has a lot of preservatives, artificial coloring, and flavoring.
Good old mayo, tastes great on sandwiches. This is a commercial version specifically engineered for long shelf life, so it has a lot of preservatives, artificial coloring, and flavoring.
Ranch dressing, great on salad or with chicken strips, fries, and burgers. This is a commercial version loaded with artificial preservatives for longer shelf life.
Teriyaki sauce. It goes well with chow mein, stir fry, or on chicken and burgers.
The red rooster! Good on just about anything savory. Not a good idea to drink it!
A large tub of mild chocolate in powdered form. Intended for baking, not mixing, but would do in a pinch for an emergency refreshment.
A large tub of commercial chocolate milk mix. Not recommended dry, but amazing when mixed!
Fruit punch powder! OH YEAAAAAAAH! Not recommended dry!
Tangy, unusually sweet orange drink mix! Not recommended dry!
Particularly sweet grape drink powder! Don't ya wanna? Not recommended dry!
Complicated. Multifaceted. Root beer! In powder form.
Orange drink from powder. Much better mixed!
The fruit punch most kids grew up with. OH YEAAAAAAAH!
Better now that it's mixed, this grape drink will take you way back. Don't you wanna?
One of the most complicated flavor mixes of all time, this is root beer, straight from powder. Delicious!
No longer solely the drink of the gods, now you too can feel elevated with some cocoa-powered sweetness!
This is chocolate milk made using baker's chocolate powder. It is bitter and milder than purpose-built drink mix, but still chocolatey enough to enjoy. Sort of.

Mass-produced national brand orange juice, loaded with artificial flavoring and preservatives. This is pulp-free and has a much sweeter less citrus flavor thanks to the added sugar. Completely devoid of health benefits!
Mass-produced national brand apple juice, loaded with artificial flavoring and preservatives. Much more pronounced sweet flavor thanks to the added sugar. Completely devoid of health benefits!

Mass-produced national brand cranberry juice, loaded with artificial flavoring and preservatives. Much more tolerable than fresh juice thanks to the added sweeteners. Completely devoid of health benefits!

Mass-produced national brand grape juice, loaded with artificial flavoring and preservatives. Tastes nothing like real grapes but in this case that's not a bad thing. Completely devoid of health benefits!

Mass-produced national brand pineapple juice. The flavor is obviously artificial, like most of the ingredients, but it still carries the sweetness of its host fruit. This is loaded to the gills with artificial preservatives and coloring to keep it shelf-stable and appealing.
Slightly sweetened all-natural concord grape juice, freshly pressed! Delicious and healthy.
The sweetest natural juice you can find: fresh pressed pineapple! And healthy for you, to boot!

Electrolytes. Sugar. Artificial fruit punch flavoring. High profile labeling. Designed for marathon runners and olympians. Even though the flavor is subdued, it's not bad tasting. But it would be better chilled.
Baby cow food, appropriated for adult humans.  Having been canned, this milk should last for a very long time.
Commercial big-brand healthy drink! Has artificial preservatives and 20% juice! Contains up to eight vegetable flavors!! Tasty and nutritious but not as healthy as fresh juiced veggies!
A whole wheel of New York style cheesecake! Still in its original packaging. What a score!
A whole wheel of marbled chocolate cheesecake! Still in its original packaging. What a score!
A whole wheel of variety sampler cheesecake! Still in its original packaging. What a score!
Red velvet cake! Smooth and luscious.
Carrot cake! Crumbly.
A pumpkin spice cake!
German chocolate cake! What a rare treat!

The cake is topped with edible paper depicting a scene of four young-looking girls with oddly-colored hair raising their arms in cheer. For some reason there are bumps in the cake where the breasts are. It makes you wonder what kind of person originally ordered this made.
A sampler tray of 4 different kinds of sliced cheeses.
A sampler tray of 4 different kinds of sliced meats.
A tray of pre-cooked unbreaded shrimp with a tartar sauce cup in the middle.
A variety tray of 3 different kinds of crackers, 2 kinds of cheese, and thin summer sausage slices.
A freshly prepared footlong sandwich composed of 3 different sliced meats, 2 different sliced cheeses, tomatoes, lettuce, onions, and a liberal smear of proprietary dressing topped off with oil.

A freshly prepared footlong veggie supreme. Has tomatoes, two different types of lettuce, both green and white onions, cucumbers, banana peppers, jalapenos, and olives drenched in a flavored olive oil dressing.
A philly cheesesteak panini.
A grilled chicken cheese panini.
This is a chicken BLT ranch wrap. It takes you back to better times, when things were simpler. When the deli was running you'd get these in halves, but looks like you get a whole wrap this time!

This is a tofu and veggie wrap. Not nearly as satisfying as a chicken wrap, but four time as good for you! When the deli was running you'd get these in halves, but looks like you get a whole wrap this time!
Fried to golden brown perfection, these salty slices are guaranteed to please. Will make you thirsty!
Thick cut potato slices, fried to a golden greasy brown and generously salted. The perfect modern complement to a burger.
Long spirals of delightfully salty, greasy potatoes.
These are corn dogs the way they were meant to be eaten - greasy, fatty, and full of flavor straight from a commercial deep fryer. Frozen corn dogs just simply can't compare.
A pair of soft-shell burritos filled with gooey beans and cheese.
A pair of soft-shell burritos filled with the works. Succulent meat. Crisp veggies. Gooey cheese. Heaping tablespoons of sour cream and guacamole.
A handful of mozzarella sticks. Gooey. Golden brown. Greasy. So worth it.
A handful of chicken sticks. The convenience of minced meat, in the convenient form of fries!
A large bell pepper, cored and stuffed with rice, beef, tomatoes, corn, and melted colbyjack cheese.
A specialty from New England's northern neighbors, this is fries drenched in a meat gravy and liberally covered with fried cheese curds.
Some corn chips with a side of habanero salsa.
Ground meat formed into a well-browned loaf in a thick gravy slathered with smoky barbeque sauce.
Succulent portabello mushrooms hollowed out and filled with rice, melted cheese, deeply browned ground meat, and roasted veggies.
Classic potato salad. Filling, but mildly thirst-provoking.
German potato salad. With the addition of diced pickles, mustard, and thick smoky bacon, it's much heartier and more savory than classic potato salad.
Mashed potatoes with a light dusting of salt, pepper, and mild spice. Served with brown gravy.
Classic macaroni salad. Refreshing.
A New England variation on the traditional tuna salad, this one instead features hake, cod, lobster, and crab, all minced with a light savory cream and robust spice blend.
Sweetened fruit chunks in a mix of their own syrup and vanilla-flavored heavy whipping cream dusted with cinnamon. Mildly good for you!
This is a breakfast casserole, a combination of eggs, milk, tater tots, bacon, and spices all baked together to a uniform golden brown.

This is a broccoli bake casserole, a combination of broccoli florets in mayonnaise and cream of chicken with herbs, topped generously with thick layers of cheese, and then baked to golden brown. Healthy, fattening, and delicious.
This is a tuna casserole.
A breaded cutlet of meat, prepared German-style.

A German hallmark, this is a soft, juicy, tender roast of meat with various herbs, seasoings, and spices. Has a sour kick to it due to having marinated in vinegar and red wine for days before roasting.

Pancakes from ground potatoes, egg, and flour. Having a neutral flavor by themselves, they go well with either savory or sweet toppings. These ones have apple sauce and sugar liberally drizzled over them.

Pancakes from ground potatoes, egg, and flour. Having a neutral flavor by themselves, they go well with either savory or sweet toppings. These ones have cottage cheese and sour cream spread over them.
A German take on quiche, this one uses rye instead of traditional wheat flour for the base, and features bacon crumbles covering the top.
Pizza in the convenience of a slimmed down hot pocket. Pepperoni and sausage in piping hot, gooey mozzarella and marinara.
A hot pocket! This one is meatball marinara with melted mozzarella.
A hot pocket! This one is ham and cheese.
A hot pocket! This one is pepperoni pizza.
A hot pocket! This one is philly cheesesteak.
A very sour beet root soup with beef stock and assorted sauteed veggies. Good for you, but not particularly palatable.

Goopy carbonara! Wavy al dente egg noodles in a thick sauce of egg, heavy cream, and parmesan finished with minced garlic, onion, and thick-cut bacon chopped into chunks. The deli version has a proprietary blend of spices and seasoning that significantly heighten the overall flavor profile.
A wheel of soft cheddar cheese.
A wheel of hard, tart cheddar cheese.
A wheel of smooth muenster cheese.
A wheel of slightly aromatic swiss cheese.
A wheel of moist, delicate colbyjack cheese.
A wheel of firm, crumbly parmesan cheese.
A wheel of creamy gouda cheese.
A two pound container of whole fat large-curd cottage cheese with high moisture content. Good on its own, or as a side dish to virtually anything. Especially good in lasagna!
A two pound container of whole fat cream cheese. Slightly tart and dry by itself, but good for baking with.
A two pound container of whole fat ricotta cheese. Slightly sweeter than cottage cheese and with about the same moisture content. Great for garnishing pastas in general.
About a pound of deli-sliced meat. This is mesquite turkey.
About a pound of deli-sliced meat. This is honey-glazed turkey.
About a pound of deli-sliced meat. This is smoked ham.
About a pound of deli-sliced meat. This is honey-baked ham.
About a pound of deli-sliced meat. This is roasted chicken.
About a pound of deli-sliced meat. This is pepper chicken.
About a pound of deli-sliced meat. This is roast beef.
A fully cooked slab of beef. This is a t-bone.
A fully cooked slab of beef. This is a ribeye.
A fully cooked slab of beef. This is a sirloin.
A fully cooked slab of beef. This is a tri-tip.
A whole bone-in chicken, roasted rotisserie-style. Juicy and filling.
A generous assortment of breaded boneless wings, thighs, and breasts. This is the teriyaki glaze.
A generous assortment of breaded boneless wings, thighs, and breasts. This is the bourbon barbeque glaze.
A generous assortment of breaded boneless wings, thighs, and breasts. This is the orange chicken glaze.
A generous assortment of breaded boneless wings, thighs, and breasts. This is the spicy general tso glaze with whole chili pods.
Deep fried breaded bone-in chicken wings, thighs, and breasts. Mild seasoning blend.
Deep fried breaded bone-in chicken wings, thighs, and breasts. Spicy seasoning blend.
Deep fried breaded bone-in chicken wings, thighs, and breasts. Barbeque glaze.
Deep fried breaded bone-in chicken wings, thighs, and breasts. Habanero glaze.
An iconic nationwide dish, this is a golden brown breaded ball of minced crab meat and finely diced savory vegetables with a signature new england herb blend.
A deep browned formed cake of minced cod fish meat, potato, onion, and herbs with an incredibly savory flavor. Served with tartar sauce. A regional specialty.
Several rings of squid meat grilled until thick and firm with a light sear.
A hollowed out cucumber 'cup' containing a blend of plain yogurt, hot sauce, and dijon mustard, with a combination of minced crabmeat and minced lobster folded in and topped with black peppercorns.
Creamy, cheesy lobster resting on a bed of fresh shredded lettuce in a whole wheat roll and drizzled with zesty lemon-flavored yogurt dressing. A traditional recipe, made portable!
Basically clam strips, but thicker and more flavorful with the same delicious deep fried breading.
Deep-fried golden-brown nuggets filled with flaky fish. The perfect side dish to any proper New England meal.
Minced salmon with a light breading shaped into a large, light patty and thoroughly browned. The northeasterner's answer to the meatloaf.
Short of whale or shark meat, this is the heartiest meat in the sea. Broiled, it's got an out-of-this-world umami profile that's well-complemented by the interspersed vegetable rounds.
Bite-sized cooked-through lobster bits in three different varieties of gooey cheese with diced onion, minced garlic, and buttery pasta. An American classic, Yankee style.
Oily stirfried noodles with veggies and meat.
Fried stuffed dumplings with cabbage and pork.
Crispy dumplings filled with cabbage and pork.
Crispy dumplings filled with cream cheese and imitation crab meat.
Thin oily slices of beef on a bed of sticky white rice with a savory sauce.
Thick chunks of pork bathed in a tangy red glaze over sticky white rice.
Slices of salty chewy beef mixed with broccoli florets doused with a savory sauce over sticky white rice.
Stir-fried tender chicken and chili pods in a spicy teriyaki sauce over sticky white rice.
A sweet, hard hollow pastry that normally has a fortune written on paper for you. This one, however, does not.
A breaded deep-fried chicken cutlet.
Steamed white rice, veggies, and teriyaki pork in a convenient bowl.
Steamed white rice, veggies, and teriyaki chicken in a convenient bowl.
Steamed white rice, veggies, and teriyaki beef in a convenient bowl.
Steamed white rice and veggies with teriyaki sauce in a convenient bowl.
Pork tenderloin cutlets in a mild savory sauce flanked by long thin strips of cabbage, broccoli, and carrots.
Shrimp in a salty sauce served over sticky white rice.
Boiled chicken broth with beaten egg wisps throughout. This version has tiny chunks of tofu and white pepper seasoning as well.
A relatively thick soup of veggies, pork broth, corn starch, white pepper, and vinegar. Very good for you.
Thick oily buckwheat noodles with tender chunks of stir-fried vegetables and chicken. Salty and delicious.
An especially thick, hearty chicken noodle soup with wide egg noodles, large chunks of chicken, and hefty slices of veggies in a savory broth.
Particularly thick slices of dark meat chicken and spicy andouille sausage in a traditional rice and veggie gumbo. Has a kick to it!
Tender cuts of sirloin steak and yukon gold potato chunks in a creamy white stock.
A New England specialty, Venus De Milo soup is thoroughly browned ground beef, diced tomatoes, mixed veggies, and orzo in a beef and onion broth.

A traditional New England preparation of the time-honored chicken and dumplings. Packed full of delicious juices and flavor. The entire chicken is used to make the initial stock, then removed, the meat is pulled off the bones, and then dropped in with bay leaves, salt and pepper, and the puffy, slightly sticky dumplings.

A New England icon, crab bisque is perfectly cooked-through crab meat in a light, creamy broth with a balanced, flavorful blend of ground ginger and minced garlic, carrot, green onion, celery heart, cayenne pepper, and dried lemon peel.

A New England twist on an American staple, firehouse chili has a mix of 5 different chopped, powdered, and crushed peppers, cinnamon, and cumin to infuse the juicy tomato, onion, carrot, beans, and beef chunks with a powerful kick. Has a little brown sugar to temper the flavor.
Beef stew done the New England way: slow-baked with fresh mushrooms, peas, tomato soup, and red wine in addition to the usual potatoes, carrots, onions, and chewy beef.
This is a local take on the world-famous New England clam chowder. It uses diced salted pork to boost the overall flavor.
A blend of multiple beans with ham, tomatoes, celery, onions, red bell peppers and generous salt.
This is clam chowder the way you expect it. Creamy. White. Slightly chewy. Great with crackers.
A mix of veggies, various wild mushrooms, and thick-cut bacon in a broth of heavy cream, white wine, and chicken stock.
Bite-sized chunks of just-through cooked hake in a creamy stock with thick potato slices, chopped onions, thick chopped bacon, and a chopped bacon and chive garnish. A regional specialty.
Succulent tiny shrimps. Chewy chopped clam. Delicate flaky haddock. Fried, crumbled bacon. All in a creamy stock with thick chunks of veggies. This is what made New England famous.
A block of extra-firm tofu, perfect for stir-frying. Not exactly palatable raw.
Cubed tofu fried in sesame oil and then soaked in soy sauce. Healthy and delicious.
Edamame, otherwise known as soy beans. With a little sauce and a beer these make a tolerable snack.
A light, flaky, crescent-shaped pastry with a smooth buttery texture.
A flaky, buttery pastry filled with apple slices in thick syrup.
A pretzel-shaped pastry filled with almond paste and custard, topped with slivered almonds, and lightly dusted with crystal sugar.
A dozen tightly pinched pastries in the shape of a 19th century tricorne, filled with marzipan and topped with rich milk chocolate.
Made from linzer pastry dough and rich vanilla buttercream. Light and delicate, like its namesake!
Flaky pastries sandwiching a sweet cloud of vanilla whipped cream and custard. Brushed with a hint of raspberry jam, New England style.
An iconic pastry filled with rich flavorful custard and topped with dark chocolate frosting.
A loaf of french bread with a slathering of garlic-infused butter on the inside, in a convenient ready-to-bake foil-lined paper bag.
Ah, the wonderful aroma of cooked garlic bread. It's amore.
A bag of thick slices of toasted white bread, each with its own chewy layer of melted butter and cheese. Because everything's bigger in Texas.
A dainty pastry covered with a thin layer of custard that is in turn overlaid with fruit syrup and fruit. This particular one is laden with raspberries.
A dainty pastry covered with a thin layer of custard that is in turn overlaid with fruit syrup and fruit. This particular one is laden with strawberries.
A dainty pastry covered with a thin layer of custard that is in turn overlaid with fruit syrup and fruit. This particular one is laden with blueberries.
A sweetened pastry rolled into a sugar-dusted tube with a generous custard cream filling. The made man's favorite food.
A traditional glazed doughnut. The sweetest reminder of the world that once was.
A chocolate frosted doughnut. Not nearly as tender and soft as a glazed doughnut, but who cares? It's chocolatey!
A powdered doughnut. Mostly dry, but still sweet and delicious!
A strawberry jam-filled doughnut. Surprisingly tangy!
A dozen sweet glazed doughnut holes. The pinnacle of bite-sized luxury!
A dozen chocolate frosted doughnut holes.
A dozen powdered doughnut holes.
A sweet vanilla cream-filled pastry covered with thick chocolate.
A soft bakery-fresh rolled pastry lined with sticky cinnamon brown sugar and covered with a thick glaze of cream.
A country classic. Moist, sweet, and squeezable.
A scone filled with New England cranberry jam. Tart, yet delicious.
A scone filled with New England blueberry jam. Sweet and delightful.
A plain bagel.
A supreme bagel with five kinds of seeds atop a light layer of toasted cheddar cheese. Secretly good for you.
A sweet pumpkin-infused pastry rolled up with buttery cream cheese and confectioner's sugar.
A sweet lemon-infused pastry rolled up with buttery cream cheese and confectioner's sugar.
This is a dozen sugar cookies, bakery fresh.
This is a dozen snickerdoodle cookies, bakery fresh.
This is a dozen chocolate chip cookies, bakery fresh.
This is a dozen rainbow m&m cookies, bakery fresh.
This is a dozen oatmeal raisin cookies, bakery fresh.
This is a dozen peanut butter cookies, bakery fresh.
This is a dozen nutella-stuffed cookies, bakery fresh.
A warm french baguette with beautiful score lines. It's almost a tragedy to eat this!
A dozen poppyseed muffins. Moderately sweet with a subtle chewiness.
A dozen blueberry muffins. Sweet, slightly dry, but with plenty of tanginess from the fresh blueberries throughout.
A dozen cinnamon coffee cake muffins. Deli-quality melted butter and brown sugar veins throughout, with a generous crumb topping of cinnamon and brown sugar. It doesn't get much better than this.
A dozen banana nut muffins. Exceptionally moist and smooth, these almost melt in your mouth.
A dozen luscious chocolate muffins. Entirely infused with chocolate, right down to thick chunks of chewy fudge and chocolate chunks throughout.
A dozen oreo chocolate muffins. Studded with oreo cookie bits and drizzled with melted oreo cream. The best kind of volcanic eruption.
A dozen pumpkin muffins. Moist and velvety, with just enough spice to bring out the edge.
A dozen pound cake muffins. Modestly sweet and buttery with a smooth glaze.
A dozen cheesecake muffins. Exceptionally rich and creamy.
A dozen bouillon cubes. These are the chicken stock variety.
A dozen bouillon cubes. These are the beef stock variety.
A dozen bouillon cubes. These are the vegetable stock variety.

Congratulations. You're living the dream. Not a hint of dryness. Perfectly slathered in layers of rich icing. Delicate and fluffy. This is what every doughnut wishes it could be.
Heavily processed mass-produced glazed buns.
Heavily processed, mass-produced, but utterly delightful cream-filled chocolate cakes covered with thick sheets of zigzag frosting.
A classic melding of chocolate and peanut butter throughout melt-in-your-mouth layers of cookie.
Artificially sweetened neatly folded pastry covered liberally with sickeningly sweet sugar and filled with gooey apple chunks in syrup.
Artificially sweetened neatly folded pastry covered liberally with sickeningly sweet sugar and filled with gooey cherry chunks in syrup.
Artificially sweetened neatly folded pastry filled with luscious chocolate pudding as a filling. Absolutely heavenly.
Heavily processed chewy chocolate cookies sandwiching an artificially flavored fudge filling.
Heavily processed cream sandwiched between two artificially flavored oatmeal cookies. A childhood favorite!
